00:09:44.942 --> 00:09:48.735
And my stance was no,
you didn't do that.

00:09:48.735 --> 00:09:49.860
Why do you get reparations?

00:09:49.860 --> 00:09:51.490
And I won an essay contest.

00:09:51.490 --> 00:09:53.240
And I read the essay,
and I was like, god,

00:09:53.240 --> 00:09:55.770
that's terrible-- no.

00:09:55.770 --> 00:09:57.640
But it's really
good to still have

00:09:57.640 --> 00:09:59.142
the record of who you were.

00:09:59.142 --> 00:10:01.350
Because you see how you've
grown, how you've changed,

00:10:01.350 --> 00:10:02.830
how your thought has changed.

00:10:02.830 --> 00:10:05.020
College changed
everything about politics

00:10:05.020 --> 00:10:07.690
and how I look at
the world at large.

00:10:07.690 --> 00:10:10.450
So who I was before college is
completely different from who I

00:10:10.450 --> 00:10:12.810
am now in terms of my beliefs.

00:10:12.810 --> 00:10:15.270
BRADLEY HOROWITZ: And I
guess how much of what

00:10:15.270 --> 00:10:17.210
