yourself, and how

00:10:17.210 --> 00:10:19.339
much do you do for others?

00:10:19.339 --> 00:10:21.130
It sounds like it was
a little bit of both.

00:10:21.130 --> 00:10:21.850
LUVVIE AJAYI: A
little bit of both,

00:10:21.850 --> 00:10:23.892
but I try to do most of
it for myself. [LAUGHING]

00:10:23.892 --> 00:10:25.391
BRADLEY HOROWITZ:
I think that's why

00:10:25.391 --> 00:10:26.970
you're so appealing, actually.

00:10:26.970 --> 00:10:29.422
LUVVIE AJAYI: Well, because
my whole thing is, OK, one,

00:10:29.422 --> 00:10:30.880
I'm not writing in
an echo chamber.

00:10:30.880 --> 00:10:33.430
So the idea that I'm just
writing for myself is false.

00:10:33.430 --> 00:10:37.550
But I am a writer
because if I don't write,

00:10:37.550 --> 00:10:39.360
the words kind of stay with me.

00:10:39.360 --> 00:10:41.160
So like I'm the
person who is taking

00:10:41.160 --> 00:10:43.470
a nap on the plane
writing blog posts, too,

00:10:43.470 --> 00:10:46.032
at the same time, which
