It's part of why you're
here today and part of why

00:13:28.450 --> 00:13:29.650
we know about you.

00:13:29.650 --> 00:13:32.710
But it's also a place where
there is a lot of hate

00:13:32.710 --> 00:13:37.130
and a lot of misinformation
and filter bubble.

00:13:37.130 --> 00:13:39.320
And I want to talk
about that experience.

00:13:39.320 --> 00:13:43.730
So we're heartbroken you've
rejected YouTube wholesale.

00:13:43.730 --> 00:13:46.700
Most of the people who aren't
here today are working on that

00:13:46.700 --> 00:13:48.600
and fixing it as we speak.

00:13:48.600 --> 00:13:51.280
So we'd like you to give it
a try tomorrow or next week.

00:13:51.280 --> 00:13:52.530
LUVVIE AJAYI: [LAUGHING] Yeah.

00:13:52.530 --> 00:13:55.120
BRADLEY HOROWITZ: But
what is your experience,

00:13:55.120 --> 00:13:55.870
both good and bad?

00:13:55.870 --> 00:13:56.920
Have you been trolled?

00:13:56.920 --> 00:13:57.970
Have you been doxxed?

00:13:57.970 --> 00:14:01.340
Have you been harmed by
social media personally?

00:14:01.340 --> 00:14:07.550
And how should we as owners
of some of the services

00:14:07.550 --> 00:14:11.410
that people use think
about what we can do?

00:14:11.410 --> 00:14:15.290
Without getting into
censorship and repressing

00:14:15.290 --> 00:14:18.190
people's feelings, how do
we create safe environments

00:14:18.190 --> 00:14:19.330
for people?

00:14:19.330 --> 00:14:21.620
LUVVIE AJAYI: OK, so my
decision to not do YouTube

00:14:21.620 --> 00:14:24.147
has been, one, because
I hate editing stuff.

00:14:24.147 --> 00:14:26.230
And again, I don't want
it to just be me talking--

00:14:26.230 --> 00:14:27.350
BRADLEY HOROWITZ: Oh,
so you're lazy is the--

00:14:27.350 --> 00:14:28.724
LUVVIE AJAYI: Lazy
is part of it.

00:14:28.724 --> 00:14:29.774
Oh, absolutely.

00:14:29.774 --> 00:14:32.190
But then the second part is I
hate the community on there,

00:14:32.190 --> 00:14:34.590
because that community
is so full of hate.

00:14:34.590 --> 00:14:37.570
Because at one point, it
was where you can actually

00:14:37.570 --> 00:14:39.000
comment anonymously.

00:14:39.000 --> 00:14:41.400
And what that spurs
is keyboard courage,

00:14:41.400 --> 00:14:45.409
people who decide that since
they are a number in a system,

00:14:45.409 --> 00:14:47.450
they can say whatever they
want, as opposed to it

00:14:47.450 --> 00:14:48.530
being attached to their names.

00:14:48.530 --> 00:14:50.863
So a lot of my friends are
YouTube stars and like people

00:14:50.863 --> 00:14:52.580
who built their
following on YouTube,

00:14:52.580 --> 00:14:55.110
like Franchesca Ramsey.

00:14:55.110 --> 00:14:56.660
And I used to see
the comments they

00:14:56.660 --> 00:14:59.630
would get all day, every day,
and to avoid the comments, they

00:14:59.630 --> 00:15:01.756
would have to sit
there moderating it,

00:15:01.756 --> 00:15:03.630
either themselves, which,
of course, triggers

00:15:03.630 --> 00:15:04.500
all types of trauma.

00:15:06.809 --> 00:15:08.350
Or they just actively
just be just be

00:15:08.350 --> 00:15:11.080
like, I threw up a video,
I just never go back

00:15:11.080 --> 00:15:12.420
into my comments section.

00:15:12.420 --> 00:15:15.000
And for me, the
power of the internet

00:15:15.000 --> 00:15:16.090
is connecting with people.

00:15:16.090 --> 00:15:17.590
And I think that's
really important.

00:15:17.590 --> 00:15:19.340
So I was like, you know what?

00:15:19.340 --> 00:15:20.310
I'm a writer.

00:15:20.310 --> 00:15:21.220
I prefer to write.

00:15:21.220 --> 00:15:21.950
I'll be writing.

00:15:21.950 --> 00:15:23.190
Y'all catch me there.

00:15:23.190 --> 00:15:24.860
I don't want to do videos yet.

00:15:24.860 --> 00:15:27.740
And I know YouTube started
fixing some of that.

00:15:27.740 --> 00:15:31.284
I was never really recruited
to come back into the fold.

00:15:31.284 --> 00:15:33.450
BRADLEY HOROWITZ: Well,
consider this an invitation.

00:15:33.450 --> 00:15:35.860
LUVVIE AJAYI: An invitation
to come back into the fold?

00:15:35.860 --> 00:15:37.780
Like I was using my Vimeo
channel, because I was like,

00:15:37.780 --> 00:15:38.363
you know what?

00:15:38.363 --> 00:15:40.030
I need to store some
video somewhere.

00:15:40.030 --> 00:15:42.330
So I just didn't feel like
YouTube was the place.

00:15:42.330 --> 00:15:44.850
Now, in terms of the
hate online and trolling,

00:15:44.850 --> 00:15:48.280
so as a black woman--
well, as a woman is one,

00:15:48.280 --> 00:15:50.710
as a black person is
another, as a black woman is

00:15:50.710 --> 00:15:53.619
another-- the type of feedback
that we get on social media

00:15:53.619 --> 00:15:55.410
is completely different
from everyone else.

00:15:55.410 --> 00:15:58.390
So this was tested out
by people on Twitter,

00:15:58.390 --> 00:16:00.290
actually, where
they did like a week

00:16:00.290 --> 00:16:03.890
where they exchanged avatars.

00:16:03.890 --> 00:16:06.400
So black women and
white men decided

00:16:06.400 --> 00:16:08.430
to do this experiment
and exchange avatars

00:16:08.430 --> 00:16:11.300
and see how the
difference in your avatar

00:16:11.300 --> 00:16:14.600
affects how the
responses you get are.

00:16:14.600 --> 00:16:16.380
And the white men who
had the black women

00:16:16.380 --> 00:16:18.460
avatars for the
week were stunned

00:16:18.460 --> 00:16:21.570
by the type of vitriol
they got for simple stuff

00:16:21.570 --> 00:16:22.810
that they were saying.

00:16:22.810 --> 00:16:27.300
For me as a side-eye sorceress
and a professional shader--

00:16:27.300 --> 00:16:28.550
[LAUGHTER]

00:16:28.550 --> 00:16:31.460
--I am lucky to not
receive some of the hate

00:16:31.460 --> 00:16:32.670
that a lot of people get.

00:16:32.670 --> 00:16:33.760
Because here's the thing.

00:16:33.760 --> 00:16:36.160
I can beat you at that game.

00:16:36.160 --> 00:16:39.110
Like I've spent all
my life being shady.

00:16:39.110 --> 00:16:40.000
I can do this.

00:16:40.000 --> 00:16:41.650
But I've been fortunate--

00:16:41.650 --> 00:16:43.390
BRADLEY HOROWITZ: The trolls are
afraid of you, is the problem.

00:16:43.390 --> 00:16:44.800
LUVVIE AJAYI: The trolls
don't come at me as much

00:16:44.800 --> 00:16:46.130
as they come at other people.

00:16:46.130 --> 00:16:47.449
I will say that.

00:16:47.449 --> 00:16:49.990
But one thing that I've loved
about my social media platforms

00:16:49.990 --> 00:16:53.830
is people saying that
my community reflects

00:16:53.830 --> 00:16:57.115
me, which is king compliment.

00:16:59.780 --> 00:17:01.830
No matter where I
am on the internet,

00:17:01.830 --> 00:17:08.829
I like to keep my spaces clear,
free of hate, and as a space

00:17:08.829 --> 00:17:10.450
you can get in a public domain.

00:17:10.450 --> 00:17:14.010
So my audience is also very
protective of the spaces

00:17:14.010 --> 00:17:15.180
that I've created.

00:17:15.180 --> 00:17:17.130
So if any type of
hate creeps through,

00:17:17.130 --> 00:17:19.030
they handle it before
I even get there.

00:17:19.030 --> 00:17:21.000
Because they understand that
this is one of the few places

00:17:21.000 --> 00:17:22.750
you can go and actually
read the comments.

00:17:22.750 --> 00:17:25.420
So how everyone else tells
you, never read the comments,

00:17:25.420 --> 00:17:28.359
you want to read the comments
on my posts on my Facebook,

00:17:28.359 --> 00:17:30.200
on my Twitter, on
anywhere that I am.

00:17:30.200 --> 00:17:33.030
Because my audience is super
smart, super thoughtful,

00:17:33.030 --> 00:17:38.400
and they've managed to maintain
a space that is actually good.

00:17:38.400 --> 00:17:40.420
And it shows the best
of humanity, as opposed

00:17:40.420 --> 00:17:43.610
to the rest of the internet,
which kind of shows awfulness.

00:17:43.610 --> 00:17:45.610
BRADLEY HOROWITZ: So I
want to talk about filter

00:17:45.610 --> 00:17:47.160
bubble, this concept.

00:17:47.160 --> 00:17:50.210
You mentioned you don't just
like to preach to the choir,

00:17:50.210 --> 00:17:50.710
right?

00:17:50.710 --> 00:17:51.950
That's part of what you do.

00:17:51.950 --> 00:17:54.980
But you also want to
reach people and change

00:17:54.980 --> 00:17:56.500
people's minds.

