00:19:31.170 --> 00:19:33.770
Because supporting him means
you support and tolerate

00:19:33.770 --> 00:19:38.060
hate and misogyny and
Islamophobia and anti-Semitism

00:19:38.060 --> 00:19:39.680
and anti-woman.

00:19:39.680 --> 00:19:42.000
And it's just anti
everything that

00:19:42.000 --> 00:19:44.550
is not straight, white male.

00:19:44.550 --> 00:19:45.740
And it's a problem.

00:19:45.740 --> 00:19:48.090
So you deleting
those people, I don't

00:19:48.090 --> 00:19:50.090
think it's necessarily
creating a filter bubble,

00:19:50.090 --> 00:19:51.200
because here's the thing.

00:19:51.200 --> 00:19:54.090
What do you learn from them
besides what you already know,

00:19:54.090 --> 00:19:56.660
which is that hate does
exist in the world?

00:19:56.660 --> 00:20:01.430
And even educated people who are
somewhat sensible and logical

00:20:01.430 --> 00:20:07.080
can still tolerate awful things
in people who perpetuate that.

00:20:07.080 --> 00:20:10.370
And I don't have the
capacity to even do that.

00:20:10.370 --> 00:20:13.857
I am not a mediator.

00:20:13.857 --> 00:20:16.190
I'm not the person you walk
up to just like, oh, my god,

00:20:16.190 --> 00:20:17.170
let me see both sides.

00:20:17.170 --> 00:20:21.940
Oh, no, I'm very much
biased about everything.

00:20:21.940 --> 00:20:22.720
So yeah.

00:20:22.720 --> 00:20:25.136
BRADLEY HOROWITZ: I've heard
you talk about the difference

00:20:25.136 --> 00:20:26.699
between journalism and writing.

00:20:26.699 --> 00:20:27.990
You consider yourself a writer.

00:20:27.990 --> 00:20:32.130
And it sort of speaks to this
biased-and-proud attitude

00:20:32.130 --> 00:20:32.730
you have.

00:20:32.730 --> 00:20:37.640
Can you talk a little
bit-- at Google,

00:20:37.640 --> 00:20:39.030
we have things like Google News.

00:20:39.030 --> 00:20:40.850
And even our search
results, we work

00:20:40.850 --> 00:20:44.090
very hard to make them fair.

00:20:44.090 --> 00:20:47.910
Talk about journalism
versus writing and maybe not

00:20:47.910 --> 00:20:49.910
only the role you
have in that spectrum,

00:20:49.910 --> 00:20:51.260
but where should Google sit?

00:20:51.260 --> 00:20:55.030
Should we be opinionated, or--?

00:20:55.030 --> 00:20:57.140
LUVVIE AJAYI: So
I do call myself

00:20:57.140 --> 00:20:58.470
a writer and not a journalist.

00:20:58.470 --> 00:21:00.350
Because I feel like
as a journalist,

00:21:00.350 --> 00:21:02.660
you do have to
maintain some level

00:21:02.660 --> 00:21:06.020
of like, what, objectivity?

00:21:06.020 --> 00:21:09.220
And just be like, I'm not
always going to choose sides.

00:21:09.220 --> 00:21:10.769
I don't know how to do that.

00:21:10.769 --> 00:21:13.060
I'm the person who can't
write-- I can't write anything

00:21:13.060 --> 00:21:14.450
but op-eds.

00:21:14.450 --> 00:21:15.860
But they'll be fact-based.

00:21:15.860 --> 00:21:17.720
So for me, I give myself
the responsibility

00:21:17.720 --> 00:21:19.470
of making sure I'm
double-checking to make

00:21:19.470 --> 00:21:21.510
sure I'm not passing
on fake news,

00:21:21.510 --> 00:21:24.780
making sure that my opinion
is based on some fact

00:21:24.780 --> 00:21:25.850
that I heard.

00:21:25.850 --> 00:21:28.400
So that is important.

00:21:28.400 --> 00:21:31.540
As a company, I
understand if Google

00:21:31.540 --> 00:21:34.750
wants to maintain
like neutral ground.

00:21:34.750 --> 00:21:37.010
So it shows both sides.

00:21:37.010 --> 00:21:40.650
But then as a person
of opinion and I

00:21:40.650 --> 00:21:43.850
think as a leader in
all things, Google

00:21:43.850 --> 00:21:46.310
might need to one
day step up and say,

00:21:46.310 --> 00:21:49.280
actually, this is the
lane that we pick.

00:21:49.280 --> 00:21:50.950
Like if somebody
goes into Google

00:21:50.950 --> 00:21:54.947
and wants to find a way
to join a hate group,

00:21:54.947 --> 00:21:56.530
I feel like it should
be a little more

00:21:56.530 --> 00:21:58.599
difficult for them
to find it, to find

00:21:58.599 --> 00:21:59.640
that type of information.

00:21:59.640 --> 00:22:02.269
Because essentially, you can
serve up information to them

00:22:02.269 --> 00:22:02.810
on a platter.

00:22:02.810 --> 00:22:06.370
And be like, just because we're
being impartial, what does that

00:22:06.370 --> 00:22:07.570
do for the world?

00:22:07.570 --> 00:22:11.161
And how does that impact
the betterness of the world?

00:22:11.161 --> 00:22:12.660
And I think Google
is a company that

00:22:12.660 --> 00:22:14.510
cares about that in some way.

00:22:14.510 --> 00:22:16.944
So to make it that easy I feel
like I would be a mistake.

00:22:16.944 --> 00:22:17.860
BRADLEY HOROWITZ: Yep.

00:22:17.860 --> 00:22:19.710
The people that aren't
working on YouTube

00:22:19.710 --> 00:22:21.254
are thinking about
that right now.

00:22:21.254 --> 00:22:22.415
[LAUGHTER]

00:22:22.415 --> 00:22:26.090
But you look at
Google, it's pretty

00:22:26.090 --> 00:22:28.720
clear we have a very
diverse workforce,

00:22:28.720 --> 00:22:30.560
just looking out
at the audience.

00:22:30.560 --> 00:22:31.370
I'm kidding.

00:22:31.370 --> 00:22:34.709
[LAUGHTER]

00:22:34.709 --> 00:22:39.341
LUVVIE AJAYI: He's like
[INAUDIBLE] [LAUGHING]

00:22:39.341 --> 00:22:41.340
BRADLEY HOROWITZ: I wish
this was representative

00:22:41.340 --> 00:22:42.220
of our workforce.

00:22:42.220 --> 00:22:44.960
Unfortunately,
this is a biased--

00:22:44.960 --> 00:22:47.232
LUVVIE AJAYI: Shout-out
to Bradley for that!

00:22:47.232 --> 00:22:49.109
[LAUGHING]

00:22:49.109 --> 00:22:50.900
BRADLEY HOROWITZ: But
we are working on it.

00:22:50.900 --> 00:22:51.990
LUVVIE AJAYI: Yeah.

00:22:51.990 --> 00:22:55.900
BRADLEY HOROWITZ: I think
we're very much in a listening

00:22:55.900 --> 00:22:56.730
and learning mode.

00:22:56.730 --> 00:23:03.310
And as we try to address this,
like any advice on that front?

00:23:03.310 --> 00:23:05.570
How do we actually
create-- the people who

00:23:05.570 --> 00:23:07.930
are creating these products,
how can they more represent

00:23:07.930 --> 00:23:09.685
the world and the audiences?

00:23:09.685 --> 00:23:11.560
LUVVIE AJAYI: Google
and other tech companies

00:23:11.560 --> 00:23:14.430
have got to start trying harder,
even harder than you are now.

00:23:14.430 --> 00:23:17.480
[APPLAUSE]

00:23:17.480 --> 00:23:19.890
Because here's the
thing, is I feel

00:23:19.890 --> 00:23:21.560
like every company
needs to reflect

00:23:21.560 --> 00:23:24.460
the world as it is for the
greater good of that company,

00:23:24.460 --> 00:23:25.290
too.

00:23:25.290 --> 00:23:27.790
Because more diverse
voices in the room,

00:23:27.790 --> 00:23:29.620
your products are going
to be even better.

00:23:29.620 --> 00:23:31.660
Because you're getting all
types of people being like,

00:23:31.660 --> 00:23:32.710
have you thought about this?

00:23:32.710 --> 00:23:33.740
No, that doesn't work.

00:23:33.740 --> 00:23:34.910
What about this?

00:23:34.910 --> 00:23:36.800
And I think it's in
your best interest

00:23:36.800 --> 00:23:40.430
to get you some more
color, get you some more

00:23:40.430 --> 00:23:42.840
people of different backgrounds
who can be in a room

00:23:42.840 --> 00:23:44.590
and be like, oh, OK,
this is what I think,

00:23:44.590 --> 00:23:47.830
and then not gets shut out by
their coworkers who are white.

00:23:47.830 --> 00:23:50.460
[APPLAUSE]

00:23:50.460 --> 00:23:52.386
Like even recently I
was reading an article

00:23:52.386 --> 00:23:54.510
about how the women in the
White House in the Obama

00:23:54.510 --> 00:23:57.740
administration have
formed like this Voltron

00:23:57.740 --> 00:24:01.460
where when they're in meetings,
if one woman says an idea,

00:24:01.460 --> 00:24:03.910
another woman repeats it,
and then somebody else

00:24:03.910 --> 00:24:07.054
repeats it who's a woman just so
the idea is not given to a man.

00:24:07.054 --> 00:24:08.470
Because we've been
in enough rooms

00:24:08.470 --> 00:24:10.857
where we say something,
and everyone is like, eh.

00:24:10.857 --> 00:24:13.190
And then the dude says it,
and they're like, great idea.

00:24:13.190 --> 00:24:17.040
You're like, word, like I
didn't just say that four times?

00:24:17.040 --> 00:24:20.773
So in that type of a way, I
think tech companies need to,

00:24:20.773 --> 00:24:23.540
one, it's not even
necessarily them

00:24:23.540 --> 00:24:25.190
having a conscious
bias to be like,

00:24:25.190 --> 00:24:27.050
I'm just only going
to hire white people.

00:24:27.050 --> 00:24:27.800
That's not it.

00:24:27.800 --> 00:24:29.850
We tend to engage
with people who

00:24:29.850 --> 00:24:31.900
are in close proximity
with us, people

00:24:31.900 --> 00:24:34.300
who look like us who are
like in our immediate circle.

00:24:34.300 --> 00:24:36.880
So those are the
people we end up

00:24:36.880 --> 00:24:38.710
telling they have
job opportunities,

00:24:38.710 --> 00:24:41.570
and those are the people who
end up basically applying.

00:24:41.570 --> 00:24:46.470
What needs to happen is the
very pointed and focused attempt

00:24:46.470 --> 00:24:48.340
to go outside of that proximity.

00:24:48.340 --> 00:24:50.420
Like go to places
where you haven't been.

00:24:50.420 --> 00:24:52.672
Ask people who don't look
like the executive team.

00:24:52.672 --> 00:24:55.130
And honestly, get some black
people on your executive team,

00:24:55.130 --> 00:24:55.630
too.

00:24:55.630 --> 00:24:56.374
Y'all need that.

00:24:56.374 --> 00:24:58.110
[APPLAUSE]

00:24:58.110 --> 00:25:00.750
But I think it's a process
that needs to start now.

00:25:00.750 --> 00:25:03.662
And people need to be very
prioritizing about it.

00:25:03.662 --> 00:25:06.120
Like it shouldn't be one of
those things that's like, if it

00:25:06.120 --> 00:25:07.130
happens, it happens.

00:25:07.130 --> 00:25:09.070
It needs to be like a focus.

00:25:09.070 --> 00:25:11.570
Because in, what,
2030 or 2040, there's

00:25:11.570 --> 00:25:14.090
going to be no ethnic
majority in the country.

00:25:14.090 --> 00:25:17.790
So it behooves Google
and Facebook and Twitter

00:25:17.790 --> 00:25:20.400
and all of them,
Apple, like everybody

00:25:20.400 --> 00:25:22.820
needs to start making
it a point to find--

00:25:22.820 --> 00:25:24.130
And it's not a quota system.

00:25:24.130 --> 00:25:26.760
It's not you being like, well,
we need four more black people,

00:25:26.760 --> 00:25:28.350
we need four
Latinos, four Asians.

00:25:28.350 --> 00:25:29.080
No.

00:25:29.080 --> 00:25:30.360
You want to find people
who are qualified,

00:25:30.360 --> 00:25:31.276
and they're out there.

00:25:31.276 --> 00:25:33.710
Like people say, I can't
find black techies.

00:25:33.710 --> 00:25:35.860
I can't find Latino techies.

00:25:35.860 --> 00:25:38.460
There are Twitter
lists of people

00:25:38.460 --> 00:25:43.410
who have 500-- that says
Black Techies at the top.

00:25:43.410 --> 00:25:44.720
So we're out here.

00:25:44.720 --> 00:25:45.590
We exist.

00:25:45.590 --> 00:25:46.140
And we--

00:25:46.140 --> 00:25:48.270
BRADLEY HOROWITZ: We do have
some competence in search.

00:25:48.270 --> 00:25:48.920
So we ought to be--

00:25:48.920 --> 00:25:49.470
[LAUGHTER]

00:25:49.470 --> 00:25:51.260
LUVVIE AJAYI: I think so, OK?

00:25:51.260 --> 00:25:55.640
Like Google is like the search
king of the entire universe,

00:25:55.640 --> 00:25:56.360
not even Earth.

00:25:56.360 --> 00:25:59.430
There are probably
aliens using Google.

00:25:59.430 --> 00:26:02.895
So you have no excuse not
to be able to find and find

00:26:02.895 --> 00:26:04.382
the people who are good.

00:26:04.382 --> 00:26:05.340
BRADLEY HOROWITZ: Yeah.

00:26:05.340 --> 00:26:06.860
Cool.

00:26:06.860 --> 00:26:08.725
[LAUGHTER]

00:26:08.725 --> 00:26:09.864
LUVVIE AJAYI: He's like--

00:26:09.864 --> 00:26:11.280
BRADLEY HOROWITZ:
So in the spirit

00:26:11.280 --> 00:26:14.309
of putting us on the spot--

00:26:14.309 --> 00:26:15.100
LUVVIE AJAYI: Yeah!

00:26:15.100 --> 00:26:15.860
BRADLEY HOROWITZ:
--me in particular,

00:26:15.860 --> 00:26:18.472
I want to share something
you recently wrote.

00:26:18.472 --> 00:26:20.740
"Another day, another hashtag.

00:26:20.740 --> 00:26:23.390
White people, you
gotta get to work now

00:26:23.390 --> 00:26:26.350
about the killings of black
people by law enforcement."

00:26:26.350 --> 00:26:28.990
You say, "White people,
I'm talking to you.

00:26:28.990 --> 00:26:30.910
This is your problem to fix.

00:26:30.910 --> 00:26:33.100
Y'all got some work to do,
because this system that

00:26:33.100 --> 00:26:36.780
y'all keep on privileging from,
you've got to help us dismantle

00:26:36.780 --> 00:26:37.280
it.

00:26:37.280 --> 00:26:40.130
Because those of us who are
black and brown, we have tried.

00:26:40.130 --> 00:26:43.280
You created this robot, and
it is yours to deactivate.

00:26:43.280 --> 00:26:45.380
My skin folk don't
have the passcode.

00:26:45.380 --> 00:26:46.955
This is your monster to slay."

00:26:46.955 --> 00:26:48.060
LUVVIE AJAYI: Word.

00:26:48.060 --> 00:26:49.018
BRADLEY HOROWITZ: Yeah.

00:26:49.018 --> 00:26:51.820
[APPLAUSE]

00:26:51.820 --> 00:26:57.440
So for those of us that
agree, where do we start?

00:26:57.440 --> 00:27:02.050
How do we become better at
helping slay the monster?

00:27:02.050 --> 00:27:05.600
LUVVIE AJAYI: Yeah, you
gotta slay the dragon, man.

00:27:05.600 --> 00:27:06.830
It's a multi-step process.

00:27:06.830 --> 00:27:11.000
And I think it comes from--
we can change policy all day,

00:27:11.000 --> 00:27:11.580
every day.

00:27:11.580 --> 00:27:13.930
But if policies change but
the hearts of the people who

00:27:13.930 --> 00:27:18.220
are in these spaces to enforce
it don't, nothing happens.

00:27:18.220 --> 00:27:25.070
So the real deep belief that
it is the job of white people

00:27:25.070 --> 00:27:28.720
to fix racism because if we
could have fixed it by now,

00:27:28.720 --> 00:27:30.020
we would have done it.

00:27:30.020 --> 00:27:31.410
And we have tried.

00:27:31.410 --> 00:27:36.690
So one, listening-- I've seen
enough conversations where

00:27:36.690 --> 00:27:39.726
people are like, here's how I
felt when this issue happened.

00:27:39.726 --> 00:27:41.600
And somebody walks in
being like, well, maybe

00:27:41.600 --> 00:27:43.950
you're just looking
at it the wrong way.

00:27:43.950 --> 00:27:45.790
I was telling you
how I felt about it,

00:27:45.790 --> 00:27:47.740
but here you are
trying to argue me down

00:27:47.740 --> 00:27:50.250
about my opinion
and my feelings,

00:27:50.250 --> 00:27:52.180
which feelings are valid.

00:27:52.180 --> 00:27:53.930
So one, listening.

00:27:53.930 --> 00:27:56.697
Two, when these things happen,
a lot of times people will say,

00:27:56.697 --> 00:27:58.530
I don't know what else
to say at this point.

00:27:58.530 --> 00:28:00.570
It's getting even worse.

00:28:00.570 --> 00:28:02.730
If you don't know what to
say, amplify the voices

00:28:02.730 --> 00:28:07.010
of those who do, so
lending your platform

00:28:07.010 --> 00:28:10.382
to people who are able to say,
this is how it's affected me.

00:28:10.382 --> 00:28:11.840
This is what I
think we need to do.

00:28:11.840 --> 00:28:14.769
So lending your platforms
to black and brown voices.

00:28:14.769 --> 00:28:16.810
I also think people need
to put their money where

00:28:16.810 --> 00:28:18.600
their hearts are.

00:28:18.600 --> 00:28:20.140
People have money.

00:28:20.140 --> 00:28:21.910
Silicon Valley has money.

00:28:21.910 --> 00:28:25.780
At the minimum, donate to
anti-racist organizations

00:28:25.780 --> 00:28:29.050
and people who are actively
doing the work to fix it,

00:28:29.050 --> 00:28:30.620
people who need the
resources and who

00:28:30.620 --> 00:28:33.010
need to get in the room.

00:28:33.010 --> 00:28:34.140
That's important.

00:28:34.140 --> 00:28:38.200
And then, some of us have all
these platforms to speak up.

00:28:38.200 --> 00:28:39.690
Speak up.

00:28:39.690 --> 00:28:40.259
Use it.

00:28:40.259 --> 00:28:41.300
Because here's the thing.

00:28:41.300 --> 00:28:43.100
I don't have a job.

00:28:43.100 --> 00:28:44.620
I could say something.

00:28:44.620 --> 00:28:46.620
Nobody's going to be like,
Luvvie, you're fired.

00:28:46.620 --> 00:28:49.740
So it is in my best interest to
use my voice, because I don't

00:28:49.740 --> 00:28:52.620
have anything to lose there.

00:28:52.620 --> 00:28:55.030
And also one thing
that we need to do,

00:28:55.030 --> 00:28:56.520
because it's like
right here, it's

00:28:56.520 --> 00:29:00.040
the lowest common denominator,
is our friends and our family

00:29:00.040 --> 00:29:00.540
members.

00:29:00.540 --> 00:29:03.400
When they say hateful
things about people

00:29:03.400 --> 00:29:06.970
who are not in our group
who are marginalized,

00:29:06.970 --> 00:29:08.020
we have to say something.

00:29:08.020 --> 00:29:09.630
And you know what
we do when we see

00:29:09.630 --> 00:29:10.880
some stupid stuff in Facebook.

00:29:10.880 --> 00:29:12.824
We'll like scroll
past and roll our eyes

00:29:12.824 --> 00:29:15.240
and be like, oh, I hate the
fact that they just said that.

00:29:15.240 --> 00:29:17.150
But we never confront it.

00:29:17.150 --> 00:29:19.320
So that person thinks it's OK.

00:29:19.320 --> 00:29:21.620
So even across the
dinner table when

00:29:21.620 --> 00:29:24.521
somebody is saying something
hateful, in that moment,

00:29:24.521 --> 00:29:26.520
you have to let them know
you can't tolerate it.

00:29:26.520 --> 00:29:30.650
Because if you let it happen and
you say nothing, you're saying

00:29:30.650 --> 00:29:31.360
it is fine.

00:29:31.360 --> 00:29:33.100
It should happen just like that.

00:29:33.100 --> 00:29:36.300
[SIGHING] Huffing and puffing
is not enough-- actively

00:29:36.300 --> 00:29:38.970
being like, hey, that's
actually not an OK statement,

00:29:38.970 --> 00:29:40.860
here's why you're wrong.

00:29:40.860 --> 00:29:42.920
And after I wrote
that piece, I actually

00:29:42.920 --> 00:29:44.830
got a lot of notes
in the two weeks

00:29:44.830 --> 00:29:47.054
afterwards from people
who had been like,

00:29:47.054 --> 00:29:48.220
I've actually taken that on.

00:29:48.220 --> 00:29:51.400
One of my friends
e-mailed me and said

00:29:51.400 --> 00:29:54.740
her husband's father always says
something racist every time.

00:29:54.740 --> 00:29:57.400
And he just scrolls past it
and shakes his head in Facebook

00:29:57.400 --> 00:29:59.310
and he's like, oh,
that irritates me.

00:29:59.310 --> 00:30:02.110
After I wrote that
piece, his father

00:30:02.110 --> 00:30:04.730
put some like racist
joke up, and he sends him

00:30:04.730 --> 00:30:08.107
a three-paragraph email
about how that was not OK.

